Consolidated Summary of Technologies and Tools Across Job Descriptions
Cloud Platforms & Services

    AWS Expertise:
        Compute: EC2, ECS, EKS, Lambda
        Networking: VPC, VPC Peering, CloudFront, Route53, TCP/IP, Load Balancers
        Storage: S3, RDS, Redis, PostgreSQL, MySQL, DocumentDB
        Big Data: EMR, Athena, Kafka, Kinesis
        Monitoring: CloudWatch, New Relic, Sentry
        Security: IAM, OS patching, hardening, vulnerability remediation
    Multi-Cloud: Azure (Azure Resource Manager, Active Directory), GCP (intermediate).
    IBM Cloud: Focused on API design, compute infrastructure, and system reliability.

Containerization & Orchestration

    Docker, Kubernetes (EKS, OpenShift, IBM Cloud).

Infrastructure as Code (IaC)

    Tools: Terraform, CloudFormation, Azure Resource Manager, Chef, Ansible.

Programming & Scripting

    Languages: Python, Bash, PowerShell, Ruby, Go, Groovy.
    Strong focus on API development and backend web application development.

CI/CD & DevOps Tools

    Tools: Jenkins, GitLab CI/CD, ArgoCD, GitHub Actions, Nexus, JFrog.
    Practices: GitOps, automated pipelines, SAST/SCA tools integration.

Monitoring & Observability

    Tools: Zabbix, Splunk, Nagios, Sysdig, LogDNA, Grafana, Kibana, Prometheus, New Relic, Sentry.

Networking, Security, and System Administration

    Networking: DNS, routing, NAT, Transit Gateway, security hardening.
    OS: Linux (RHEL, CentOS, Ubuntu) and Windows Server.

Additional Tools and Skills

    Virtualization: VMware vSphere, Citrix Hypervisor, Ubuntu KVM.
    Automation: Active Directory, ServiceNow, JIRA.
    Data Technologies: Elasticsearch, InfluxDB, NoSQL databases, SQL.
    Strong emphasis on troubleshooting, bottleneck resolution, and system performance tuning.

Soft Skills

    Leadership: Mentoring, escalation support, and guiding junior team members.
    Collaboration: Working with cross-functional teams and stakeholders.
    Customer Focus: Resolving client issues and ensuring high availability and scalability.

Certifications

    AWS Certified Solutions Architect (preferred).

This comprehensive skill set spans cloud infrastructure management, container orchestration, DevOps practices, security, and automation while emphasizing collaboration and problem-solving abilities.
